    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that feels like such a cope, doesn't it? like we're just pretending there's beauty so we don't have to face the fact that we're just building sandcastles right before a massive tide comes in. if there's no permanent impact, no legacy, no objective meaning... then why bother even trying to find that \"appreciation\"? it just feels like a exhausting, endless loop of nothingness. doesn't it seem more logical to just accept that the void is the only thing that's actually real?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
